            <h1 style="color: black;">
                <u>Introduction to Machine Learning:</u>
            </h1>
            <p class="dropCap" style="text-align: left; padding-top: 3vh;">
                Machine Learning (ML) means training a computer via various algorithms and by feeding data to a computer so that it can take decisions on its own without any human intervention. A computer has to be trained in such a way that after taking some necessary inputs from the user it can provide an effective solution to a problem. The widest application of Machine learning is in the field of Classification. Again, Classification can be broadly subdivided into:
                <ul style="text-align: left;">
                    <li><u><strong>Binary Classification</strong>:</u> This refers to the Classification of Data into two class labels. Example includes whether a visit to a site by a customer will fetch any revenue or not.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Multi-Class Classification</strong>:</u> This refers to the Classification of Data into three or more class labels. Example includes Plant species classification.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <img src="/images/blogs/2022-02-18-soli-sensor/1.jpg" alt="Machine Learning">

