        <div class="second">
            <h1 style="color: black; padding-top: 2vh;">
                <u>Introduction to Computer Vision:</u>
            </h1>
            <p style="text-align: left; padding-top: 1vh;">
                Computer Vision and Machine Learning are two fields which are closely related to each other. Computer Vision involves a lot of things. One application of Computer Vision is Recognition. Recognition in computer vision involves object recognition, identification, and detection. Some specialized tasks of recognition are optical character recognition, image retrieval, and facial recognition.
                <ul style="text-align: left;">
                    <li><u><strong>Machine learning approach of recognition</strong>:</u> Here, a pre-defined database exists where key points of objects are defined and stored beforehand. While categorizing an image, the key points are checked and hence matches are found according to that.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Motion Analysis</strong>:</u> Digital videos are processed here to produce information. Movements of objects are recorded and categorization is done as per that.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Application in Autonomous Vehicles</strong>:</u> Cameras are fitted on top of self-driving cars for 360 degree vision and a range of 250 m. The cameras aid in finding lane, estimating road curvature, detection of obstacle, traffic sign detection and many more.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <img src="/images/blogs/2022-02-18-soli-sensor/2.jpg" alt="Machine Learning">
