            <h1 style="color: black; padding-top: 2vh;">
                <u>Introduction to SOLI Sensor:</u>
            </h1>
            <p style="text-align: left; padding-top: 1vh;">
                SOLI understands human motion (Smart detection) at various angles (360 degree sensing) from finger taps to body movements. SOLI has been designed in such a way that the interaction feels human. 
            </p>
        </div>

        <br>

        <div class="fourth">
            <h1 style="color: black; padding-top: 2vh;">
                <u>Library of Movements:</u>
            </h1>
            <p style="text-align: left; padding-top: 1vh;">
                The SOLI library consists of three basic units of interaction that can be used to build complex interactive experiences. The basic units are as follows:
                <ul style="text-align: left;">
                    <li><u><strong>Aware</strong>:</u> Whenever a person is around the sensing area, SOLI becomes aware of the location of that person.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Engaged</strong>:</u> SOLI recognizes the body cues that indicate the starting or ending of an interaction.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Active</strong>:</u> Here, SOLI responds to various movements for performing specific tasks.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <img src="/images/blogs/2022-02-18-soli-sensor/3.jpg" alt="Machine Learning">
        </div>

        <br>

        <div class="fifth">
            <h1 style="color: black; padding-top: 2vh;">
                <u>SOLI Technology:</u>
            </h1>
            <p style="text-align: left; padding-top: 1vh;">
                The ML Model has been designed in such a way that it is able to a large range of possible movements. The working principle is as follows:
                <ul style="text-align: left;">
                    <li><u><strong>Emission</strong>:</u> SOLI radar emits electromagnetic waves, which interacts with nearby objects such as human hands and hence the energy of the emitted signal gets scattered and some portion are reflected back towards the radar antenna.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Reflection</strong>:</u> The properties of the reflected signal such as energy, time delay, etc. capture important information regarding the object including, size, shape, distance, material, etc.</li>
                    <li><u><strong>Recognition</strong>:</u> By analyzing the characteristics of the reflected signal, SOLI can distinguish complex movements within its field.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>

        <br>

        <div class="sixth">
            <h1 style="color: black; padding-top: 2vh;">
                <u>One Powerful Chip:</u>
            </h1>
            <p style="text-align: left; padding-top: 1vh;">
                The design of the SOLI chip reduces complexity and consumes very low power. Unlike traditional radars, SOLI has no moving hardware components. The efficient implementation of the algorithms enables interaction at low power and is cost-effective.
            </p>

